Reviewed `ARCHITECTURE.md`, `GUIDE.md`, and `EVALUATIONS.md`.

The aligned guidance preserves the one-engine thesis:
- architecture says the core engine owns ordered history, lineage, manifests, and recovery
- processors and materializers remain first-party-adjacent instead of becoming a separate semantic path
- the same contract is described as shared across embedded and server packaging
- CRDTs are described as optional overlays inside materializers rather than base stream semantics

This satisfies SRS-NFR-02.
